story_txt:
My name is Kathryn Roberts. I earned my BFA from Goddard College, where I also served as the managing editor for the literary journal Guideword. My fiction, creative nonfiction, and poetry has appeared in various journals, both online and in print. I've worked as a freelance writer and pastry chef for the better part of the past decade. While at Goddard, I wrote the first draft of a short novel, Companion Plants. The book will be published by Fomite Press, a small independent publisher, this spring.Companion Plants started as a short story about a young woman figuring out her sexuality in contrast to her religion. But, the piece skirted around what I really wanted--needed--to say. Quite frankly, I was too scared to put anything down on paper that I thought my family wouldn't want to read. That is, until my mentor (and Goddard advisor), the great Ryan Boudinot, told me exactly what I needed to hear:"Right now there’s a
thirteen year-old girl who desperately needs to read what you have to say. She
needs to read about sex and religion in precisely the way you’re writing about
these subjects in order for her to be happy. The discomfort of those close to
you is far outweighed by the needs of those people you’ll never know, who’ll
only know you by your words. You’re writing to express something that they
themselves cannot express."I took Ryan's words as my mantra and expanded Companion Plants. After years of writing, wringing my hands, and revising, I finished the novel. In the book, a young woman blames her religious upbringing for a friend's suicide and sets out to discover who she is beyond the strict rules of doctrine. Reinventing herself in a new town, she struggles with breaking the taboos of her mother's faith and navigating the lines between friend and lover, child and adult. As she learns new details about events back home, she is forced to reevaluate the childhood she thought she knew. An excerpt from the novel was published and can be read here: Slush Pile Magazine.Now: this Indiegogo campaign. I am thrilled by the upcoming publication of my novel, both on a personal achievement level and because I will finally be able to reach other people with the story. But, as my book is coming out through an independent press, and with the publishing industry the way it is today, I am entirely responsible for promotion with no financial help from the publisher. This promotion includes a website, advertising (such as a book trailer and promotional bookmarks), supplying the cover art and author photo, and touring/giving readings.As a writer who worked a variety of full-time (and then some) jobs to put myself through school and complete my novel, publication with a small press is the chance of a lifetime. The opportunity to get my name out there and potentially get work picked up by a major publishing house later on. But to maximize this opportunity, I need your help!What I Need & What You GetAll of the money I raise will be put toward promoting my novel. This includes:
Payment for the cover art (photograph of Trinidad cliffs by Krista Sappington);
An author/book website;
A book trailer (my inability to make a video for Indiegogo is an indicator of my need for a professional!);
Promotional bookmarks, to be distributed through libraries, stores, and an online bookseller;
Travel across the east coast and, with enough raised funds, the rest of the country to give readings and promote the book, focusing on independent bookstores.
Any money raised beyond the initial goal will allow me to host readings in more cities across the U.S. and reach a wider audience with my novel.Your support will make my dream of being a successful novelist a very real possibility by allowing me to make the most of this opportunity. Plus, you'll support independent publishers and bookstores in the process. You'll be keeping alive a centuries-old tradition of art patronage. Just call yourself Medici.In return, you will receive:
For $5: a personal, hand-written thank you card and a supporter credit on the Companion Plants website;
For $10: a personal, hand-written thank you card, a supporter credit on the website, and a Companion Plants bookmark;
For $35: a personal, hand-written thank you card, a supporter credit on the website, a Companion Plants bookmark, PLUS a copy of the novel;
For $50: a personal, hand-written thank you card, a supporter credit on the website, a Companion Plants bookmark, PLUS a signed copy of the novel inscribed to whomever you choose;
For $100: a personal, hand-written thank you card, a supporter credit on the website, a Companion Plants bookmark, a copy of the novel, PLUS a box of homemade cookies (made by me from one of the recipes I developed while working as a pastry chef) and a copy of the recipe;
For $250: a personal, hand-written thank you card, a supporter credit on the website, a Companion Plants bookmark, a copy of the novel, PLUS a limited edition print of an ink drawing depicting a scene or character from the novel;
For $500: a personal, hand-written thank you card, a supporter credit on the website, a Companion Plants bookmark, a copy of the novel, PLUS Reconciliation: Recipes to Rebuild Your Relationship, the Companion Plants cookbook featuring recipes developed by me during my time as a pastry chef and cook, and notes on beverage pairings contributed by sommelier Dominic Miller;
For $750: a personal, hand-written thank you card, a supporter credit on the website, a Companion Plants bookmark, a copy of the novel and the cookbook, PLUS the original block from one of the limited edition prints depicting a scene or character from the novel; or
For $1,000: a personal, hand-written thank you card, a supporter credit on the website, a Companion Plants bookmark, a copy of the novel and the cookbook, PLUS 10 copies of Companion Plants signed and donated in your name to the recipients of your choosing.
Other Ways You Can HelpIf you'd like to contribute but are unable to do so financially, please consider spreading the word about my campaign and my novel. Link to Facebook, say something on Twitter, you know the drill. Indiegogo makes it easy with those little share buttons. I will be endlessly appreciative!Thank you so much for your help!
